    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is offset by the direct applicability of the ASTM F1717 protocol to the COU and the cross-laboratory validation evidence. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds. The FEA framework is accepted for use in the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending prediction COU at Medium assurance level.",
